<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-676-399  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 676 399.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Design  Nov 1 1990 v29 n21 p119(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A more sensible approach to VHDL synthesis. (very-high-speedintegrated circuit hardware description language)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Mendes da Costa, Robert.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Many designers convinced that top-down design using VHDL and logicsynthesis tools will lead to increased productivity are concernedabout the difficulty of adopting such a methodology.andP;  Severalproblems have been encountered by design teams using the firstVHDL synthesis tools, including the inability to correlate thesynthesized schematics with the source VHDL description, theinability to target programmable logic device andfield-programmable gate array technologies, differences betweensimulation and synthesis libraries, the inability to incorporateexisting design expertise and the relatively steep learning curveof the technique.andP;  Companies must consider their approach to VHDLsynthesis carefully and develop one that is integral to the designprocess, tightly integrated into the electronic design automationenvironment and more flexible in terms of the needs and expertiseof designers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Electronic Design AutomationComputer-Aided DesignVery High Speed Integrated CircuitsHardware Description LanguagesCircuit DesignMethodsSoftware SelectionIntegrated SystemsProgram Libraries.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>